[Amit Varma]: Horace what do you think of your earlier books do you look back and you think that oh you know

02:42:12.760 --> 02:42:17.800
[Amit Varma]: i wish i could do it better or oh i really love it it captured that moment what where i was at that

02:42:17.800 --> 02:42:22.600
[Amit Varma]: moment or do you think that oh another person wrote it it wasn't me i am now somebody else

02:42:22.600 --> 02:42:28.520
[Guest]: how do you look at your past work and you know there's some of it i hate yeah i do hate some of

02:42:28.520 --> 02:42:33.720
[Guest]: it uh but i can see why i wrote it at that point and i can see the flaws but there are some things

02:42:33.720 --> 02:42:38.360
[Guest]: that i wrote that i like even now and i think oh that's that did i really write that you know that

02:42:38.360 --> 02:42:43.080
[Guest]: kind of feeling but i mean like what are those well there's one story i wrote which was very

02:42:43.080 --> 02:42:49.160
[Guest]: close to me in my heart because it was actually something that happened and i was kind of uh

02:42:49.160 --> 02:42:56.120
[Guest]: uh changing it for the fiction but it did happen and it it was a story which of my i mean my

02:42:56.120 --> 02:43:00.680
[Guest]: collection is called that it's called Ababil Ki Udaan which is the flight of the swallow so it's

02:43:00.680 --> 02:43:07.480
[Guest]: about death and it's about superstition so this uh i mean it's about this little girl and it

02:43:07.480 --> 02:43:12.680
[Guest]: actually happened to me but obviously in a story changes but the death of her brother for instance

02:43:12.680 --> 02:43:20.120
[Guest]: so it's uh in the story the brother dies and she's somehow uh how can i say this without

02:43:20.120 --> 02:43:24.840
[Guest]: revealing the whole story i mean she's uh thinking about death and all these sort of

02:43:24.840 --> 02:43:30.280
[Guest]: things that come in all these little details that come in she's lying on the lawn and this brother

02:43:30.280 --> 02:43:34.520
[Guest]: she she comes running on the lawn and the brother is lying on the lawn and she jumps over him and

02:43:34.520 --> 02:43:39.880
[Guest]: she thinks it's about superstition so she's been told that if you jump over a person who's lying

